# Regulatory Crosswalk: TradFi to Web3

Objective: To map traditional financial regulatory requirements (NYDFS, FFIEC, MAS) to technical and operational controls in a decentralized environment.

| Traditional Control | Web3 Equivalent / Implementation |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Multi-Factor Auth (MFA)** | Multisig (Safe/Gnosis), Hardware Security Modules (HSM), MPC Custody |
| **Identity Management (IAM)** | Role-based multisig signing, Whitelisting, Soulbound Tokens (SBT) |
| **Change Management** | On-chain Governance, Timelocks, Smart Contract Upgradeability Analysis |
| **Incident Reporting** | Real-time on-chain monitoring (Forta/Tenderly), Protocol circuit breakers |
| **Segregation of Duties** | Multisig threshold requirements (m-of-n), separated Treasury vs. Op wallets |

### Framework Focus
- **NIST CSF Alignment:** Applying Identify-Protect-Detect-Respond-Recover to vault architecture.
- **FFIEC Compliance:** Ensuring auditable custody and transaction lifecycle history.
